NUMBER 112
NAME Grymwood, entrance
*DESCRIPTION_START
Standing on a mound of dirt, you view the world around you. A wall of naked gray trees stretches as far as you can see, climbing into the Teeth of Shartan in the distant north. At first glance, the forest looks to be an impenetrable barrier of twisted branches, but a track of footprints through the new snow say otherwise.
*DESCRIPTION_END
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
ITEM 8 1567
EXIT NE 115
EXIT S 560
EXIT ABOVE 2141
IFVERB RECALL -1
	IFVAR SKILL32 >= 3
		ECHO PLAYER Grymwood is reputed to be enchanted by children who died before their time.
	ENDIF
ENDIF
FOREST
DAY_LIGHT
;
NUMBER 110
NAME Grymwood, Matriarch Tree
MONSTER_GROUP 10
ITEM 9 693
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
Suddenly the undergrowth clears and you find yourself at the base of an enormous tree. Its red, brown, fibrous trunk is easily as wide as a house. It grows straight up and out of sight above the canopy. Mighty branches sprout regularly from its sides. Gnarled roots dig into the ground like giant fingers. Beneath the snow cover crunches a heavy layer of needle- like leaves. Nearly buried in a snowdrift, there appears to be a small opening at the base of the trunk.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 8 1567
EXIT S 111
EXIT NE 117
ITEM 0 72 ADJ1=294 VAL2=109
IFVERB RECALL -1
	IFVAR SKILL32 >= 5
		ECHO PLAYER This giant post-cataclysmic redwood tree was the hideout of Vashaska, reputed consort of Dahkahn, and a powerful, evil necromancer in her own right. If you recall the story correctly, she agreed to execute her own children as the price for power. Dahkahn grew weary of her anyway and slew her for his amusement one night. Ironically, her soul remains trapped in this great tree, the Matriarch Tree: mother of all the other trees in the forest.
	ENDIF
ENDIF
FOREST
DAY_LIGHT
