NUMBER 111
NAME Grymwood, rubber plants
MONSTER_GROUP 10
ITEM 9 693
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
The undergrowth is robust here. Big plants, with huge rubbery leaves, crowd out the other vegitation. A thin layer of snow coats the thick leaves and a few delicate icicles hang precariously. As you push the leaves aside to pass, the branches spring back into place, giving you a good swat on the behind. Every time this happens you get the feeling that someone is laughing.
*DESCRIPTION_END
