NUMBER 160
NAME Matriarch Tree, crown
ITEM 9 693
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
The crown of the tree is about fifteen feet wide -- enough room for a
hippogriff to land. Looking out you have a stunning panoramic view. North
are the Teeth of Shartan, somewhat less formidable from this altitude. East
is the forest canopy, stark and skeletal. Beyond that, a crater mars the
land. Its edges are jagged clay peaks that look like miniature mountains.
