MONSTER_GROUP 54
ITEM 9 693
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
Fog blankets the entire area here, even obscuring the bridge somewhat. A ledge runs around the mountain disappearing into the vapor. Interesting footprints can be seen clearly in the dust below when you look down.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 8 1567
MOUNTAIN
OBSCURED_DAY_LIGHT
LIMITED_VISION
EXIT ABOVE 2199
ITEM 0 61 ADJ1=222 ADJ2=262
ITEM 1 302
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
This rickety bridge uses rope as a handrail and wooden planks for a base. Here and there, planks appear missing. Even though it is long and sways slightly in the wind, it seems stable enough to cross.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFVERB GO 0
	IFVAR WEIGHTWEQ > 400
		ECHO OTHERS %N starts across the bridge, then runs back quickly as it begins to sag and groan under their weight!
		ECHO PLAYER You start across the bridge, but within a few seconds you realize the bridge is sagging much more than it should, and the groaning of the ropes tells you that you definitely should not be crossing this bridge.
  ENDIF
  IFVAR WEIGHTWEQ <= 400
		ECHO OTHERS %N cautiously crosses the bridge.
		MOVE 629
		AFFECT 629
		ECHO OTHERS Suddenly, %n steps out of the fog.
		AFFECT 628
	ENDIF
	CLEARVERB
ENDIF
EXIT SE 631
EXIT NE 637
IFVERB RECALL -1
	IFVAR SKILL32 = 1
		ECHO PLAYER These tracks are definitely larger than the animals you would expect here.
	ENDIF
	IFVAR SKILL32 = 2
		ECHO PLAYER These tracks are much larger than any animals that should be in this area. Not only that, but they look fresh, as if made just recently.
	ENDIF
	IFVAR SKILL32 > 2
		ECHO PLAYER These trackers are much larger than any anumals that should be in this area. Not only that, but they look fresh, as if made just recently. The print looks characteristic of a troll.
	ENDIF
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 633
NAME Paegar Bridge, boulder side
MONSTER_GROUP 54
ITEM 9 693
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
Spanning the distance between two neighboring mountains, this old rickety bridge extends from this peak to one that is east. A ledge skirts the mountain perimeter in either direction. Below, there is a fatal looking drop.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 8 1567
MOUNTAIN
DAY_LIGHT
EXIT NW 634
EXIT SW 636
EXIT ABOVE 2196
ITEM 0 61 ADJ1=222 ADJ2=262
ITEM 1 367
IFVERB EXAM 0
  ECHO PLAYER With rope handrails and wooden floor boards, this bridge dips sharply in the middle before rising again at the other end. It seems stable enough, and if its age has anything to do with its strength, then it should support an average human's weight with no problem.
ENDIF
IFVERB GO 0
	IFVAR WEIGHTWEQ > 400
		ECHO OTHERS %N starts across the bridge, then runs back to safety when the rope ends begin to creak!
		ECHO PLAYER You begin to cross the bridge, but your weight seems to cause the bridge to sag more than you would expect, and soon you hear the creaking of the ropes at the end! You decide to run back to safety.
		AFFECT 626
		ECHO OTHERS You see %n start across the bridge from the boulder side and turn back.
		AFFECT 625
	ENDIF
	IFVAR WEIGHTWEQ <= 400
		ECHO PLAYER You cautiously begin across the bridge, ready to make a run for either end if you have to.
		ECHO OTHERS %N cautiously begins across the bridge.
		MOVE 626
		AFFECT 626
		ECHO OTHERS %N crosses the bridge to you.
		AFFECT 625
	ENDIF
	CLEARVERB
ENDIF
