CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
A thick layer of smooth ice covers this large boulder, which stands partway out into the icy, freezing waters of the mountian stream. A second boulder, nearly as large as this one, stands on the opposite bank of the stream. Although the ice on the boulder provides little traction, the top of the opposite boulder is just a short jump away from this one.
