The valley closes down around the stream here, becoming not so much a valley as a narrow gorge through the rocks. The water of the freezes as it tumbles down the steep gorge and over the huge rocks strewn about its bed, coating the rocks and gorge with a sparkling layer of ice. An ancient bridge of rough-hewn uquart logs spans the stream, its timbers buried beneath the deep winter snowdrifts.
*DESCRIPTION_END
