NUMBER 720
NAME Teeth of Shartan, bridge
ITEM 9 693
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
Beneath the snow, well aged uquart logs form this sturdy bridge across the
stream. The builder of this bridge clearly knew his craft well, for despite
the added load of a foot of snow, the bridge is still quite sound. Upstream,
a splendid cataract of solid ice has formed in the narrow raceway that the
stream flows down. Thousands of icicles, from the size of an uquart needle
to the size of a frost giant, form an unbroken cascade from top to bottom.
To the east, buried beneath a snowdrift, lies a small stand of stunted uquart,
and to the west, a road leads down the mountain valley.
*DESCRIPTION_END
