CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
A few small, gnarled uquart trees stand sparsely about this snowy hollow, which is surrounded on three sides by towering cliffs. The rocky cliffs are covered with huge ice formations, the result of a small but steady flow of water out of the rocks. In the center of the hollow, stands the delapidated ruin of an ancient hearth, buried to the mantle beneath the snow. A sturdy bridge of lashed uquart logs crosses to the other bank.
*DESCRIPTION_END
