*DESCRIPTION_START
A small creek trickles out from a dark opening in the rock face here, its water steaming in the cold mountain air. A few of the smooth streambed stones have been deliberately placed in a circle around the creek to collect its waters in a still pool before they join the rushing torrent of the mountain stream. Oddly, the water in the pool hasn't frozen hard like most of the other pools along this bank.
