CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
A titanic wall of rock rises from the streambed to the lofty peaks, diverting the flow of the water around it. From a thousand tiny pores in the wall come an equal number of spectacular ice formations, each a slightly different shade of blue, making the cliff look as if it were made of crystal. Upstream, a bank of worn streambed rocks, pushed by eons of flowing water, has piled up behind the obstruction, forming an ice encrusted beach
*DESCRIPTION_END
