ITEM 9 693
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
A pile of broken rock and other rubble lies buried beneath a heap of dirty snow, the remains of past rockslides and avalanches. A wide chute cut into the bare rock above is no doubt the source of the pile. One unfortunate uquart tree, uprooted by a past slide, has struggled to survive among the loose rocks and beneath a large boulder despite the unnatural angle of its trunk and the mound of snow which now covers most of its branches and needles.
*DESCRIPTION_END
