NUMBER 733
NAME Teeth of Shartan, dam top
ITEM 9 693
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
The view from atop this earthenwork dam is breathtaking. Behind the dam, an
ice-covered lake lies nestled among several rocky, snow-covered peaks. Due
north, across the lake, a single peak rises high above all others of the
range. At the summit of this magnificent mountain is a massive formation of
broken rocks, which are draped in the icy white robes of winter. Unlike the
majority of the surrounding peaks, this one is more or less flat on top,
almost as if it had been sheared off some distance below its summit in some
great cataclysmic event. The road skirts the edge of the lake to
the northwest and northeast.
*DESCRIPTION_END
