CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
This narrow ledge provides a welcome rest for weary climbers, for although the climb on the face below is nearly vertical, the rest of the climb is along an icy overhang which thrusts outward from the mountain. A narrow crevice packed with fresh snow provides the only purchase in the smooth rock above, and the climb down the snow covered face from here is nearly as difficult.
*DESCRIPTION_END
