NUMBER 744
NAME Fang of Shartan, summit
ITEM 9 693
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
From atop this lofty peak the entire valley below seems insignificant and
tiny. The roaring mountain stream is but a pale ribbon of silver, and even
the lake seems puny compared to the grandeur of the mountain. What seemed
a flattened, broken peak from below is now clearly something very different;
the top of the mountain is a ring of rock surrounding a wide, flat,
snow-covered basin. A snow covered trail leads down through the rocks
towards the middle of the basin, and narrow crevice provides some minimal
footing for the dangerous climb down the icy mountain face.
*DESCRIPTION_END
