NUMBER 905
NAME Mirdaal, Garden
ITEM 9 693
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
Ages ago a very large cavern near the surface collapsed, leaving a space open to the sky and weather which the people of Mirdaal turned into a garden. The pebble path to the north is covered with deep snow and once-manicured hedges barely claw their way from drifts. The western door leads back underground.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 8 1567
OUTDOOR_OTHER
DAY_LIGHT
EXIT N 903
ITEM 0 340
EXIT ABOVE 2115
; hedges
ITEM 1 66 ADJ1=25 ADJ2=449 VAL2=904 UNLOCKED
; black peeling door
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
The thick confusion of broken branches and sharp thorns makes it nearly impossible to tell where one hedge ends and another begins. Small rustlings and whispering chitters emanate from well within the fortress of tangled growth.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFTOUCH 0
	CLEARVERB
	ECHO PLAYER You prick yourself on some nasty thorns you didn't see through the thick foliage.
	ECHO OTHERS %N grimaces as %s pricks %iself on some nasty thorns in the hedge.
ENDIF
